HackingTool condenses a large pentest workflow into one menu-driven repo. Instead of juggling separate installs, you get categorized access to tools for web testing, wireless security, password attacks, and recon. That makes it easier to standardize audits, demos, and lab work across different targets.

https://github.com/Z4nzu/hackingtool

